The paper deals with wireless communication networks and their optimization for higher data rates and energy efficiency. The paper discusses various optimization problems related to beamforming and resource allocation, which are typical topics in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with interference-limited networks, which is a topic in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multi-antenna systems, which is a topic in the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories.
